      COVARIANCES, July, 2011, S. Hoblit, BNL                     1428 1451
New BNL estimates in the resonances region were obtained with     1428 1451
the kernel approach. We note that resonance region for Si         1428 1451
extends to fairly high energies, in particular for 28-Si up       1428 1451
to 2.7 MeV. Included in our evaluation were resonance parameter   1428 1451
uncertainties taken over from Atlas of Neutron Resonances.        1428 1451
Dominant contribution to elastic scattering uncertainties         1428 1451
comes from the uncertainty of the scattering radius R'.           1428 1451
Covariances in the resonance region were merged with the          1428 1451
covariances in the fast neutron region taken from the             1428 1451
ENDF/B-VI.8. We reviewed the latter data and concluded            1428 1451
that they are reasonable with the exception of MT=104             1428 1451
covariances which were considered to be problematic               1428 1451
and hence they have been removed.                                 1428 1451
